name: Hot Zucchini Chips Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 220Â°C. Line a baking tray with baking paper.
Lightly whisk 2 eggs in a shallow bowl and season with pepper. Combine cup polenta, cup finely grated parmesan, 1 tsp salt and 1 tsp garlic powder in a second shallow bowl.

Trim ends from 500g small zucchini, cut into quarters or sixths lengthwise depending on size. Dip each piece into egg then toss in polenta mixture to coat. Place on tray and bake for 15-20 minutes or until golden. Serve with good quality aioli, if desired.
